Document: InputEventMouse
Path: godot/classes/class_inputeventmouse.rst
Summary: Represents mouse input events in Godot, including position, button states, and modifiers.

Inherits: InputEvent < InputEventMouseButton < InputEventMouse

This class handles mouse-related input events, capturing details like cursor position, button presses, and keyboard modifiers. It extends InputEventMouseButton by adding mouse-specific properties and inherits from the base InputEvent class. Key properties include mouse button states, position coordinates, and modifier keys (Shift, Ctrl, etc.). Events are generated when the mouse moves, buttons are pressed/released, or modifiers change. The class is used by the InputMap system to map mouse actions to signals and functions in Godot projects.
