Document: InputEventMouse
Path: godot/classes/class_inputeventmouse.rst
Summary: Mouse input event properties including button masks, device identifiers, and position data.

- button_mask (bitfield): The mouse button mask. Default: 0.
- device (int): The input device. Overrides the base class's device property. Default: 32.
- global_position (Vector2): The global position of the mouse event. Default: Vector2(0, 0).
- position (Vector2): The local position of the mouse event. Default: Vector2(0, 0).
---CHUNK---
Document: InputEventMouse
Path: godot/classes/class_inputeventmouse.rst
Summary: Mouse input event properties including button mask and position data with context-specific behavior.

button_mask (bitfield[MouseButtonMask]): The mouse button mask identifier, one of or a bitwise combination of the MouseButton button masks. Default: 0. Set via set_button_mask(value), Get via get_button_mask().

global_position (Vector2): Returns mouse position in root Viewport coordinate system when received in Node._input() or Node._unhandled_input(). Returns mouse position in the CanvasLayer coordinate system when received in Control._gui_input(). Default: Vector2(0, 0). Set via set_global_position(value), Get via get_global_position().

position (Vector2): Returns mouse position in the Viewport coordinate system of the Node's containing Viewport when received in Node._input() or Node._unhandled_input(). Returns mouse position in the Control's local coordinate system when received in Control._gui_input(). Default: Vector2(0, 0). Set via set_position(value), Get via get_position().